article.description: Utah guard Marie Ferdinand scored a career-high 27 points and backcourtmate Jennifer Azzi added a season-high 18 to lead the Starzz to a 79-71 victory over the Indiana Fever on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Ferdinand downplays big scoring outing
article.linkText: Ferdinand's career night leads Starzz past Fever
article.story:
SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Utah guard Marie Ferdinand scored a
career-high 27 points and backcourtmate Jennifer Azzi added a
season-high 18 to lead the Starzz to a 79-71 victory over the
Indiana Fever on Tuesday night.

	   Azzi made four free throws over the final 40 seconds to put the
game out of Indiana's reach. She finished 4-of-5 from 3-point range
and had six assists.

	   Ferdinand was 11-for-18 from the field.

	   "I guess it was just one of those games that players have,''
she said. "I don't think it was one of those games where I was on
fire. I just had a lot of good looks.''

	   Indiana coach Nell Fortner was impressed with Ferdinand.

	   "We just don't have anybody with quickness to keep up with
her,'' Fortner said. "I don't know anybody who has what it takes
to guard her.''

	   The Starzz (6-3) controlled the tempo by dominating the boards
with a 41-27 rebound advantage. Utah had 13 offensive rebounds and
24 second-chance points.

	   Forward Natalie Williams led Utah with nine rebounds.

	   "The statistic that speaks to me the loudest is what we did on
the boards,'' Starzz coach Candi Harvey said. "Natalie owned the
boards tonight and was a huge difference for us.''

	   The Fever (4-5) led by as many as 11 points in the first half by
running against the bigger Starzz, but Utah adjusted defensively
and pulled within two points at halftime.

	   "We regrouped. We turned it into a halfcourt game,'' Harvey
said. "That's one of the best comebacks that I've seen our team
have.''

	   Indiana rookie Tamika Catchings was quieted by the defense of
Adrienne Goodson. Catchings finished with 14 points and 11
rebounds.

	   Starzz center Margo Dydek recorded her fourth-straight
double-double with 12 points and 12 rebounds.
